First Lady Michelle Obama, Dr. Biden, and Prince Harry will be visiting Fort Belvoir as part of their Joining Forces initiative and in support of the upcoming Invictus Games. They will meet with wounded Servicemen and women in recovery and rehabilitation programs, tour the USO Warrior and Family Center, and watch a short adaptive sports event. The visit aims to highlight innovative programming designed to support the mental health and wellbeing of service members, veterans, and their families. The Invictus Games is an international adaptive sporting event for wounded, injured, and ill Servicemen and women, and the Invictus Games Orlando 2016 will take place in May.